{"questionId":"14507839","questionHtml":"<p>On the following axes, sketch the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2c11ee4555a4b33549c10b40945b3630a0386614.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/15f76d0f2ec5b9b0392cd7ed3810e43de7fafd5e.png\"> <em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note</strong>: Award marks as follows:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for approximately correct roots, in the intervals&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for y-intercept AND local minimum in approximately correct positions. Allow for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;for local minimum&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for approximately correct endpoints, with the left end in the intervals</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://